author: PA News Agency
title: Christmas Eve worshippers to face security screening at Cologne cathedral | Somerset County Gazette
text: Cologne police acting on indications of a possible attack searched Germany’s landmark cathedral with sniffer dogs on Saturday and said worshippers attending Christmas Eve Mass would undergo security screening before being allowed in. In Austria, police in Vienna also said they were taking heightened security measures around churches and Christmas markets, deploying both uniformed and plainclothes officers. Neither police agency specified the threat, but the German news agency dpa said authorities were responding to signs of a possible attack by Islamic extremists, without citing a specific source. Michael Esser, head of the criminal investigation department of the Cologne police, said in a news release that the threat indications pointed to New Year’s Eve rather than Christmas, but added that “we are putting everything possible in motion for the security of cathedral visitors on Christmas Eve”. Cologne’s towering cathedral, whose twin spires are 157 metres (515 feet) tall, is a major tourist destination visited by some six million people a year. Police and cathedral officials urged those attending Mass on Sunday evening to arrive early and not bring bags or purses. The European Union’s home affairs commissioner, Ylva Johansson, warned on December 5 that Europe faces a “huge risk of terrorist attacks” over the Christmas holidays due to fall-out from the war between Israel and the Palestinian militant group Hamas. title: An Unbiased View of How To Lose Weight With Diabetes
text:
Getting insight right into the landscape of weight loss
Talking about weight decrease isn't only about accomplishing a version's number from a glossy publication. It's incorporated by a larger narrative regarding obtaining and preserving optimum wellness. Nevertheless, not all weight loss solutions are produced equivalent. The effectiveness of weight loss techniques can vary substantially, and this overview aims to debunk them.
Browsing the Diet Regimen Labyrinth
When it involves weight loss, there's no single method that benefits everyone. Different diets may be more reliable for various individuals, such as ketogenic diet plans, periodic fasting, or plant-based diet plans, and it is very important to find the approach that functions finest for your individual needs and lifestyle.
Reducing Weight with Ketogenic Diet Regimen
The ketogenic diet plan, aka the fat-burning diet, has actually absolutely transformed heads in recent times. This diet regimen champs high-fat, moderate-protein, and low-carbohydrate dishes.
Advocates of this diet plan commonly go crazy regarding its quick weight loss results, yet critics test its sustainability over expanded durations. The reduced appetite element is frequently overshadowed by issues concerning prospective long-lasting shortages in vitamins and minerals, examining its security.
The ketogenic diet plan is just one of the best weight loss diets for 2024 for those that intend to attain fast and dramatic modifications in their body make-up. By limiting carbs, the body gets in a state of ketosis, where it sheds fat for fuel as opposed to sugar. This can result in considerable weight loss, especially in the abdominal area.
However, the ketogenic diet also has some drawbacks that might influence its weight loss effectiveness and weight loss sustainability. A few of the typical adverse effects of this diet regimen include fatigue, headache, queasiness, constipation, negative breath, and raised risk of kidney stones. Moreover, the ketogenic diet can be tough to adhere to for a long time, as it calls for stringent adherence to a limited series of foods and might create social isolation or monotony.
Therefore, the ketogenic diet plan may not be appropriate for everyone, and it is recommended to seek advice from a physician prior to beginning it. It is likewise essential to keep track of blood degrees of ketones, sugar, and electrolytes, and to supplement with minerals and vitamins if needed.
Time-Restricted Consuming: A Guide to Intermittent Fasting
Periodic fasting reinvents standard notions of meal timing by introducing an organized consuming timetable as component of weight loss approaches. This approach highlights not only the material of meals, however also the timing of usage. Advocates of recurring fasting case that it can cause considerable weight loss throughout fasting periods. Nevertheless, taking on a fasting/non-fasting consuming regimen might pose obstacles for some people, potentially causing initial discomfort or reduced power levels. Recurring fasting is a popular choice among the top weight loss diet regimens for 2024. It entails rotating periods of eating and fasting, such as fasting for 16 hours and eating for 8 hours each day, or fasting for 24 hr a couple of days weekly. By lowering calorie intake, improving metabolic rate, and optimizing hormonal agent feature, intermittent fasting can add to weight loss. In addition, it may boost blood sugar level control, minimize swelling, and offer protection against chronic diseases.
However, recurring fasting has constraints that must be thought about when reviewing its benefits and drawbacks for weight loss. Typical obstacles consist of feelings of hunger, irritation, migraines, difficulty sleeping, and reduced performance. In addition, not everyone may be suited for periodic fasting, particularly people with clinical conditions such as diabetes, low high blood pressure, or consuming problems, as well as those who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or undernourished. As a result, it is essential to approach intermittent fasting cautiously and seek advice from a health care expert. In addition, it is important to focus on nutritious foods during the consuming window and preserve proper hydration throughout the day.
Using the Prospective of Diets Based Upon Plants
Advocates of plant-based diets tout their effectiveness in promoting weight loss, and completely factor. By concentrating on plant-derived foods such as vegetables, grains, nuts, seeds, legumes, and fruits, people can gain a host of advantages, including naturally lower fat and calorie matters, raised fiber content, and a wider series of necessary nutrients. Nonetheless, it is very important to keep in mind that careful meal preparation and potentially some supplements are necessary to guarantee appropriate healthy protein consumption and nutrient harmonizing.
Despite these challenges, a plant-based diet regimen can be a healthy and efficient technique to weight loss, as it emphasizes the consumption of whole, minimally refined plant foods while limiting or avoiding pet items. This dietary technique can create a calorie shortage, boost satiation, and boost metabolic process, every one of which can add to weight loss. Additionally, it has actually been revealed to decrease the danger of weight problems, diabetes mellitus, heart problem, and some cancers.
However, it is essential to be conscious of the possible mistakes of a plant-based diet plan, such as poor healthy protein intake, prospective shortages in iron, calcium, vitamin B12, and omega-3 fatty acids, and problem finding suitable choices when dining in restaurants or taking a trip. Some individuals may additionally locate it difficult to adhere to a plant-based diet plan, particularly those that are utilized to consuming pet products or have strong choices or yearnings.
To make sure ideal nutrition and wellness, it's necessary to thoroughly plan and monitor a plant-based diet plan. Consulting a dietitian or a doctor before starting this diet is likewise suggested, and taking supplements might be necessary to deal with any nutrient deficiencies. With proper planning and implementation, a plant-based diet plan can be a healthy and efficient method to accomplish weight loss and enhance general health and wellness.
Focusing on the information: Effective workout sessions
Beyond the diet regimen element of weight loss, incorporating physical activity-- specifically consistent workouts-- likewise plays an essential duty in achieving weight loss results.
High-Intensity Period Training (HIIT)
High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT) is a quick and intense exercise that can aid burn calories successfully.
It uses benefits beyond the health club, like the afterburn impact, which adds to general calorie burn.
HIIT is considered among the leading exercises for weight loss in 2024, as it includes brief ruptureds of extreme exercise adhered to by periods of rest or low-intensity task, duplicated for a set number of times or period.
HIIT help in weight loss by raising calorie burn throughout and after the exercise, improving cardiovascular physical fitness, and preserving muscular tissue mass. It additionally boosts insulin level of sensitivity, decreases high blood pressure, and reduces abdominal fat.
However, there are some disadvantages to HIIT that must be thought about when evaluating its advantages and disadvantages for weight loss. These consist of the danger of injury, overtraining, and exhaustion. Furthermore, HIIT may not be suitable for people with particular medical problems or those that are brand-new to exercise or have reduced fitness degrees.
To securely take part in HIIT, it is crucial to work out caution and have guidance from a fitness specialist. It is likewise recommended to heat up previously and cool down after the workout, vary the strength and duration of the intervals, and enable enough recovery time in between sessions.
Yoga exercise's Calming Result
While yoga may not be the very first thing that comes to mind when considering weight loss, integrating it right into your routine can have a substantial impact on your weight loss trip. The physical positions and holding them for prolonged durations can aid construct muscle, which consequently can enhance your relaxing metabolic rate and enhance your calorie melt.
Yoga is a holistic practice that integrates physical activities, taking a breath workouts, and meditation, making it a wonderful option for those trying to find a mind-body technique to weight loss. It can
Learn morealso improve muscle mass tone, and flexibility, and decrease anxiety, all of which can add to a much healthier and a lot more sustainable weight loss trip.
Nonetheless, it is necessary to keep in mind that yoga alone might not suffice to achieve substantial weight loss, and it is very important to combine it with a well balanced diet and healthy lifestyle practices for optimum outcomes. Furthermore, locating the ideal design and degree of yoga exercise, finding out correct placement and strategy, and preventing injuries or pressures can be obstacles that might influence its efficiency and sustainability.
Regularly Asked Inquiries
How much weight can I shed in a week?
The amount of weight that you can shed in a week depends upon many elements, such as your current weight, your calorie consumption, your calorie expense, your metabolic process, your hormones, and your genetics. Nevertheless, a safe and healthy and balanced price of weight loss is regarding 1 to 2 pounds each week, which can be accomplished by developing a calorie deficit of 500 to 1000 calories each day.
How several calories should I consume to shed weight?
The number of calories that you ought to eat to slim down relies on many elements, such as your age, height, weight, activity degree, and objective weight. Nonetheless, a basic guideline is to multiply your weight in extra pounds by 10 to 12 to obtain your everyday calorie requires for weight loss. For example, if you consider 150 pounds, you ought to consume between 1500 and 1800 calories daily to reduce weight.
The ideal food choices for weight loss are those that are nutrient-dense, reduced in caloric content, and efficient in satiating appetite. Instances of such foods include fruits, vegetables, whole grains, legumes, nuts, seeds, lean healthy protein resources, and healthy fats. Consuming these foods can help in weight loss by offering crucial vitamins, minerals, antioxidants, fiber, healthy protein, and healthy and balanced fats, while additionally promoting feelings of fullness and power.
What are the most effective workouts to do to reduce weight?
The most effective exercises to do to reduce weight are those that shed a whole lot of calories, construct and tone your muscular tissues, and boost your cardiovascular and respiratory wellness. These workouts consist of HIIT, weight training, and yoga exercise. These exercises can help you drop weight by boosting your metabolism, shedding even more calories, and protecting your muscular tissue mass.
How can I remain motivated and consistent on my weight loss trip?
The very best means to stay determined and regular on your weight loss journey are to establish wise objectives, keep a journal, reward yourself, and be positive. These suggestions can aid you lose weight by offering you a clear and realistic direction, a way to track your progression, a sense of success and satisfaction, and a favorable frame of mind and mindset.

author: Silvia Rodríguez
title: México avanza en disminución de la pobreza y en aumento de la igualdad: ONU
text:
La Organización de Naciones Unidas (ONU) aseguró que México ha tenido avances importantes en la disminución de la pobreza y el aumento de la igualdad, y reafirmó su compromiso para avanzar en el cumplimiento de la Agenda 2030 y del desarrollo sostenible en la administración de Claudia Sheinbaum.
“Las 25 agencias, fondos y programas presentes en México nos ponemos a disposición del nuevo gobierno para acompañar con nuestras capacidades y experiencia internacional a las prioridades del gobierno de Claudia Sheinbaum plasmadas en los 100 pasos para la transformación”, dijo el coordinador residente del sistema de Naciones Unidas en México, Peter Grohman.
“Cuenten con nosotros para que al final de la nueva administración que está por comenzar, cuando los estados miembros de la ONU tienen que evaluar los resultados de los 15 años de la Agenda 2030, México siga compartiendo con el mundo los ejemplos, que seguramente va a haber, esfuerzos y logros muy notables en materia de desarrollo sostenible”, añadió.
Lee:
México es uno de los países de la OCDE con más confianza en su Gobierno
Durante su participación en la presentación del “4o. Informe Nacional Voluntario 2024. Avance colectivo hacia el cumplimiento de los ODS”, Peter Grohman aseguró que la economía mexicana es sólida, con beneficios históricos para los trabajadores, programas y transferencias universales para grupos de población vulnerables y la presencia del Estado en la generación de bienes públicos estratégicos, así como nuevas prácticas de participación social.
“Estos y otros avances han derivado en menor pobreza, mayor igualdad, una gobernanza fortalecida y perspectivas de prosperidad sostenida para las generaciones presentes y futuras…(..)… México será un ejemplo inspirador al dar cuenta de que la solidaridad empieza en casa”, aseveró.
El coordinador residente del sistema de Naciones Unidas en México recordó que la Agenda 2030 integra el bienestar de las personas, el medio ambiente y la economía, también el disminuir las desigualdades y hacer todo esto mediante una cooperación internacional justa que reconozca la historia, el contexto y las prioridades de cada país.
En este sentido, destacó que México reafirmó su compromiso con el multilateralismo y el humanismo, pues en los últimos años el país se ha concentrado en dar prioridad a las personas y regiones históricamente más olvidadas, con lo que ha fortalecido la inclusión y la cohesión social que tanto se necesita para un mundo próspero y en paz.

title: Ascentage Pharma To Present Data from Two Clinical Studies at 2025 ASCO Annual Meeting, Including Oral Presentation on Its Key Assets Lisaftoclax and Alrizomadlin | AAPG Stock News
text:
Ascentage Pharma To Present Data from Two Clinical Studies at 2025 ASCO Annual Meeting, Including Oral Presentation on Its Key Assets Lisaftoclax and Alrizomadlin
Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ: AAPG) will present data from two clinical studies at the 2025 ASCO Annual Meeting. The presentations include an oral report on a Phase Ib/II study of lisaftoclax combination regimen for myeloid malignancies and a poster presentation on alrizomadlin for advanced adenoid cystic carcinoma.
The oral presentation will focus on lisaftoclax (APG-2575) combined with azacitidine in patients with treatment-naïve or prior venetoclax-exposed myeloid malignancies. The poster presentation will showcase results from a Phase 2 study of alrizomadlin (APG-115) with or without toripalimab in patients with advanced ACC or other solid tumors.
This marks Ascentage's eighth consecutive year presenting at ASCO, which will be held both online and in-person at McCormick Place, Chicago, from May 30-June 3, 2025.
Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ: AAPG) presenterà i dati di due studi clinici al Meeting Annuale ASCO 2025. Le presentazioni includono un rapporto orale su uno studio di Fase Ib/II del regime combinato con lisaftoclax per le neoplasie mieloidi e una presentazione poster su alrizomadlin per il carcinoma adenoideo cistico avanzato.
La presentazione orale si concentrerà su lisaftoclax (APG-2575) in combinazione con azacitidina in pazienti con neoplasie mieloidi naïve al trattamento o precedentemente esposti a venetoclax. La presentazione poster mostrerà i risultati di uno studio di Fase 2 su alrizomadlin (APG-115), con o senza toripalimab, in pazienti con ACC avanzato o altri tumori solidi.
Questa sarà l’ottava partecipazione consecutiva di Ascentage ad ASCO, che si terrà sia online che in presenza presso il McCormick Place di Chicago, dal 30 maggio al 3 giugno 2025.
Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ: AAPG) presentará datos de dos estudios clínicos en la Reunión Anual ASCO 2025. Las presentaciones incluyen un informe oral sobre un estudio de Fase Ib/II del régimen combinado con lisaftoclax para malignidades mieloides y una presentación en póster sobre alrizomadlin para carcinoma adenoide quístico avanzado.
La presentación oral se centrará en lisaftoclax (APG-2575) combinado con azacitidina en pacientes con malignidades mieloides sin tratamiento previo o expuestos anteriormente a venetoclax. La presentación en póster mostrará los resultados de un estudio de Fase 2 de alrizomadlin (APG-115), con o sin toripalimab, en pacientes con carcinoma adenoide quístico avanzado u otros tumores sólidos.
Esta será la octava participación consecutiva de Ascentage en ASCO, que se realizará tanto en línea como presencialmente en McCormick Place, Chicago, del 30 de mayo al 3 de junio de 2025.
Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ: AAPG)는 2025년 ASCO 연례 회의에서 두 건의 임상 연구 데이터를 발표할 예정입니다. 발표 내용에는 골수성 악성종양에 대한 lisaftoclax 병용 요법의 1b/2상 연구 구두 발표와 진행성 선양낭암에 대한 alrizomadlin 포스터 발표가 포함됩니다.
구두 발표는 치료 경험이 없거나 이전에 venetoclax에 노출된 골수성 악성종양 환자에서 azacitidine과 병용한 lisaftoclax (APG-2575)에 중점을 둡니다. 포스터 발표는 진행성 ACC 또는 기타 고형암 환자를 대상으로 한 alrizomadlin (APG-115)의 단독 또는 toripalimab 병용 2상 연구 결과를 소개합니다.
이번 발표는 Ascentage가 ASCO에 연속으로 8년째 참여하는 것으로, 2025년 5월 30일부터 6월 3일까지 시카고 맥코믹 플레이스에서 온라인과 오프라인으로 동시에 진행됩니다.
Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ : AAPG) présentera des données issues de deux études cliniques lors du Congrès annuel ASCO 2025. Les présentations incluent un exposé oral sur une étude de phase Ib/II du régime combiné à base de lisaftoclax pour les malignités myéloïdes, ainsi qu’une présentation par poster sur l’alrizomadlin dans le carcinome adénoïde kystique avancé.
L’exposé oral portera sur le lisaftoclax (APG-2575) en association avec l’azacitidine chez des patients atteints de malignités myéloïdes naïfs de traitement ou exposés antérieurement au venetoclax. La présentation par poster mettra en avant les résultats d’une étude de phase 2 sur l’alrizomadlin (APG-115) avec ou sans toripalimab chez des patients atteints d’ACC avancé ou d’autres tumeurs solides.
Il s’agit de la huitième année consécutive qu’Ascentage participe à ASCO, qui se tiendra en ligne et en présentiel au McCormick Place de Chicago, du 30 mai au 3 juin 2025.
Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ: AAPG) wird auf dem ASCO-Jahrestreffen 2025 Daten aus zwei klinischen Studien präsentieren. Die Präsentationen umfassen einen mündlichen Bericht über eine Phase Ib/II-Studie zum Kombinationstherapie-Regime mit Lisaftoclax bei myeloiden Malignomen sowie eine Posterpräsentation zu Alrizomadlin bei fortgeschrittenem adenoidzystischem Karzinom.
Die mündliche Präsentation konzentriert sich auf Lisaftoclax (APG-2575) in Kombination mit Azacitidin bei Patienten mit unbehandelten oder zuvor mit Venetoclax behandelten myeloiden Malignomen. Die Posterpräsentation zeigt Ergebnisse einer Phase-2-Studie mit Alrizomadlin (APG-115) mit oder ohne Toripalimab bei Patienten mit fortgeschrittenem ACC oder anderen soliden Tumoren.
Dies ist das achte Jahr in Folge, in dem Ascentage auf der ASCO präsentiert, die vom 30. Mai bis 3. Juni 2025 sowohl online als auch vor Ort im McCormick Place in Chicago stattfinden wird.
- Selected for oral presentation at prestigious ASCO Annual Meeting, indicating significant clinical findings
- Eighth consecutive year of presence at ASCO, demonstrating consistent research progress
- Advancing two key drug candidates in multiple cancer indications
- Both drug candidates are still investigational and not approved in the U.S.
- Final trial results and regulatory approval timeline remain uncertain
ROCKVILLE, Md. and SUZHOU, China, April 23, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Ascentage Pharma (NASDAQ: AAPG; HKEX: 6855), a global biopharmaceutical company engaged in discovering, developing, and commercializing therapies to address global unmet medical needs primarily for hematological malignancies, today announced that results from two clinical studies of the Bcl-2 selective inhibitor lisaftoclax (APG-2575) and the MDM2-p53 inhibitor alrizomadlin (APG-115), two key drug candidates in the company’s apoptosis-targeted pipeline, have been selected for presentations at the 2025 American Society of Clinical Oncology (ASCO) Annual Meeting. These presentations will include an oral report featuring updated results from a Phase Ib/II study of a lisaftoclax combination regimen in patients with myeloid malignancies.
The ASCO Annual Meeting showcases the most cutting-edge research in clinical oncology and state-of-the-art advanced cancer therapies and is the world’s most influential and prominent scientific gathering of the clinical oncology community, bringing together more than 40,000 oncology professionals from across the globe. This year’s ASCO Annual Meeting will take place both online and in-person at McCormick Place, Chicago, IL, the United States, on May 30–June 3 (local time).
Dr. Yifan Zhai, Chief Medical Officer of Ascentage Pharma, said, “We are honored to return to the ASCO Annual Meeting for the eighth consecutive year to present the latest data on our novel assets and highlight the strength of our clinical development and global innovation. We look forward to sharing an oral presentation on a lisaftoclax combination regimen in patients with treatment-naïve or prior venetoclax-exposed myeloid malignancies and a readout on alrizomadlin in patients with advanced adenoid cystic carcinoma or other solid tumors. These presentations reflect our deep focus on advancing global clinical development of our key assets in order to bring more treatment options to patients as soon as possible.”
The clinical studies to be presented at this year’s ASCO Annual Meeting are as follows:
Phase 1b/2 study of lisaftoclax (APG-2575) combined with azacitidine (AZA) in patients (pts) with treatment-naïve (TN) or prior venetoclax (VEN)-exposed myeloid malignancies
- Abstract#: 6505
- Format: Oral Presentation
- Session Title: Hematologic Malignancies—Leukemia, Myelodysplastic Syndromes, and Allotransplant
- Date and Time: Monday June 2, 2025, 3:00 PM-6:00 PM, Central Time (Tuesday June 3, 2025, 4:00 AM-7:00 AM, Beijing Time)
- Principal Authors: Michael Francis Leahy, MBChB, Royal Perth Hospital, Australia; Shaun Fleming, MBBS(Hons), PhD, The Alfred Hospital & Australian Centre for Blood Diseases, Australia; Patricia Kropf, MD, Novant Health Cancer Institute, United States, et al.
A phase 2 study of novel MDM2 inhibitor alrizomadlin (APG-115) with or without toripalimab in patients (pts) with advanced adenoid cystic carcinoma (ACC) or other solid tumors.
- Abstract#: 6102
- Format: Poster Presentation
- Session Title: Head and Neck Cancer
- Date and Time: Monday June 2, 2025, 9:00 AM-12:00 PM, Central Time (Monday June 2, 2025, 10:00 PM – 1:00 AM the next day, Beijing Time)
- Principal Authors: Ye Guo, MD, Department of Medical Oncology, Shanghai East Hospital, China; Ning Li, MD, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences Cancer Hospital, China; Xing Zhang, MD, Melanoma and Sarcoma Medical Oncology Unit, Sun Yat-sen University Cancer Center, China; Meiyu Fang, MD, Department of Rare Cancer & Head and Neck Medical Oncology, Cancer Hospital of the University of Chinese Academy of Sciences, China; Shuhang Wang, MD, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences Cancer Hospital, China, et al.
*Lisaftoclax and alrizomadlin are investigational drugs and are not approved in the U.S.
About Ascentage Pharma
Ascentage Pharma is a global, integrated biopharmaceutical company engaged in discovering, developing, and commercializing therapies to address global unmet medical needs primarily in hematological malignancies. Ascentage Pharma has been listed on the Main Board of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong Limited with the stock code 6855.HK since October 2019 and has also been listed on the Nasdaq Global Market under the ticker symbol “AAPG” since January 2025.
The company has built a rich pipeline of innovative drug candidates that includes inhibitors targeting key proteins in the apoptotic pathway, such as Bcl-2 and MDM2-p53; and next-generation TKIs that target kinase mutants emergent during cancer treatment. Ascentage Pharma is also the only company in the world with active clinical programs targeting all known key apoptosis regulators.
Olverembatinib, one of the company’s lead assets, is approved in China, with all of its approved indications included in the China National Reimbursement Drug List (NRDL). Meanwhile, a New Drug Application (NDA) for another one of Ascentage Pharmas key drug candidates, the novel Bcl-2 selective inhibitor lisaftoclax (APG-2575), has been accepted and granted a Priority Review designation by the China Center for Drug Evaluation.
To date, Ascentage Pharma has obtained a total of 16 Orphan Drug Designations from the US FDA and 1 Orphan Designation from the European Medicines Agency of the European Union for 4 of the company’s investigational drug candidates. Leveraging its robust R&D capabilities, Ascentage Pharma has built a portfolio of global intellectual property rights and entered into global partnerships and other relationships with numerous leading biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies such as Takeda, Merck, AstraZeneca, Pfizer and Innovent; and research and development relationships with leading research institutions such as Mayo Clinic, Dana-Farber Cancer Institute, National Cancer Institute (NCI) and the University of Michigan.
The company has built a talented team with a wealth of global experience in the discovery and development of innovative drugs and fully functional commercial manufacturing and Sales & Marketing teams. One pivotal aim of Ascentage Pharma is to continuously strengthen its R&D capabilities and accelerate its clinical development programs, in order to fulfill its mission of addressing unmet clinical needs in China and around the world for the benefit of more patients.
